  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR - NFI distribution for newly arrived IDPs from Ninawa to Dibaga Camp</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will bring about significant change to the lives of those in Iraq who have fled conflict in Ninewa governorate as a result of the military operation to liberate Mosul from ISIS. NIHR have conducted a rapid needs assessment identifying the newly arrived households to the camp and their priority unmet needs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide life-saving assistance to the newly arrived IDP households in Debaga camp in Makhmur.  This will be achieved through the distribution of NFI kits (2 sets of clothes, 1 pair of shoes, 1 blanket,  1 mattress and 1pillow) to 165 newly arrived households.</narrative>
  </description>
